## Classes

The outermost container in Java is a **Class**.
Every line of code you write must live inside a Class.

```java
class MyFirstProgram {
  // Code goes here
}
```

The name of the class should start with a Capital letter, and the contents go inside the curly braces `{ }`.

This is almost exactly what the main method looks like. Don't worry about memorizing these keywords just yet. Just know that this is the **Starting Line** for your app.

```java
public static void main(String[] args) {
  // Your instructions go here
}
```

slides.codeSnippet:
class Main {
  public static void main(String[] args) {
    System.out.println("Hello World");
  }
}
